# Sandbox developer env — copy to sandbox/.env (gitignored) and fill in.
#
# Loaded automatically by:
#   - sandbox/.zshrc      (the interactive sandbox shell)
#   - the "daemon" VS Code task (so autopilotd sees the provider key)
#
# Plain KEY=value lines; they're sourced with `set -a`, so no `export` needed.

# REQUIRED: which provider to run. There is no silent default anymore — the
# daemon exits at startup if this (or default_profile in config.toml) isn't
# set. Simple path: just this plus the matching key below, no config.toml
# needed at all.
# ZSH_AUTOPILOT_PROVIDER=codestral

# Provider API keys, one per brand preset. Only the one matching
# ZSH_AUTOPILOT_PROVIDER needs to be set. ollama needs none (local, no key).
# ZSH_AUTOPILOT_GROQ_KEY=
# ZSH_AUTOPILOT_ANTHROPIC_KEY=
# ZSH_AUTOPILOT_CODESTRAL_KEY=

# Phase 2 config: point the daemon at a gitignored config.toml in this dir
# (copy config.toml.example) for profile overrides or the "openai" escape
# hatch (custom OpenAI-compatible endpoints). Only needed beyond the simple
# two-var path above. A profile named by ZSH_AUTOPILOT_PROVIDER that isn't in
# the config file is fine if it's a known brand (falls back to that brand's
# preset) — an unrecognized name is a startup error.
# ZSH_AUTOPILOT_CONFIG=/abs/path/to/zeta/sandbox/config.toml

# Optional overrides applied on top of the selected provider's preset/profile.
# ZSH_AUTOPILOT_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
# ZSH_AUTOPILOT_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile
